


=Taxes=

==Description==

The Taxes application is used to define and manage tax rates applied to products, quotes, and invoices.
It serves as a central repository of tax types such as VAT, sales tax, or exemptions.
Each record includes the name, rate, and status, ensuring consistent tax application across the entire ERP system.

==List view==

[../../../../../ujest/snaps/test-screenshots-js-screenshots-sales-taxes-list-en-us-1-snap.png]

The following fields are displayed in the list view:

- Name: Descriptive label of the tax (e.g., VAT 21%, Exempt).
- Value: Tax percentage rate to be applied.
- Active: Indicates if the tax is currently available for selection.


==Form view==

This view is used to create, view or edit tax entries.

In **create** mode, a new tax rule can be defined.

[../../../../../ujest/snaps/test-screenshots-js-screenshots-sales-taxes-create-en-us-1-snap.png]

In **view** mode, tax details are visible but not editable.

[../../../../../ujest/snaps/test-screenshots-js-screenshots-sales-taxes-view-1-en-us-1-snap.png]

In **edit** mode, existing values can be updated.

[../../../../../ujest/snaps/test-screenshots-js-screenshots-sales-taxes-edit-1-en-us-1-snap.png]

The form includes the following fields:

- Name: Tax name shown in product and invoice forms.
- Value: Numeric percentage of the tax (e.g., 21 for 21%).
- Active: Allows enabling or disabling the tax for use in the system.


==Delete==

Taxes can only be deleted if they are not used in any invoice or product.

If a tax is in use, it must be deactivated instead to preserve system integrity.
